28 February 2017DEPUTY MINISTERS COLLABORATE TO CONDUCT A JOINT POST-SoNA INFORMATION SEMINAR AND YOUTH CAREER EXPO AT COFFEE BAY, EASTERN CAPEThe Deputy Ministers of Communications, Public Enterprises, Labour, Tourism and Eastern Cape MEC for Rural Development and Agrarian Reform; accompanied by the Deputy Ministers of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Transport and Water and Sanitation; will conduct a joint Post-SoNA Information Seminar and Youth Career EXPO in Coffee Bay, Eastern Cape.The two-day programme, which is an integral part of the establishment of Coffee Bay into a town; will take place on the 3rd and 4th March 2017.Conducted on the heels of the President s State of the Nation Address, post-SoNA information seminars enable government to engage with South Africans in every corner of the country and reflect on service delivery, plans, milestones and challenges faced by communities.In the same breadth, the Youth Career EXPO will:Members of the media are hereby invited to the above-mentioned outreach programme which will take place as follows:PART ONE: SUMMIT AND YOUTH CAREER EXPODate: Friday, 3 March 2017 Time: 08h00 16h30 Venue: Coffee Bay (near White Clay Beach)PART TWO: IMBIZO AND POST-SoNA INFORMATION SEMINARDate: Saturday, 4 March 2017 Time: 09h00 14h30 Venue: Coffee Bay (near White Clay Beach)Journalists will be afforded interviews and photo opportunities. RSVPs: Vuyani Sibene Cell: 073 576 3381 E-mail: vuyani@gcis.gov.zaEnquiries: Nandipa Sondati Cell: 072 611 3990Nthabeleng Mokitimi-Dlamini Cell: 073 222 5522Issued by Ministry of Communications